The move I made is not bad either, as it creates a thorn in the centre which cannot be easily removed (d4). I spent 10 minutes (from 1 hr 2 min to 52 min left) considering the disadvantages of weak pawn on d4, but found it well placed there. And if d4 pawn cannot be destroyed, then it creates nice space advantage for black.

[1 hr 3 min left] I was surprised at this slow move. The position is roughly equal, and black has some space advantage. In my opinion White should concentrate their forces for an attack of the kingside. Thus 13. f4 or 13. Qh5 can be considered. Without confrontation black can concentrate his effort on getting hold of c and d files. Alternatively, 13. c3 had to be played, as d4 pawn hinders white's development.

[48 min left] Rook on c8 is a long-term bonus. Now a number of threats appear, such as b5-b5, or Nd5-f6 with Bb7-d5. Fritz likes 13... Qd7 and 13... Qc7 too.

[1 hr 1 min left] White's move has no purpose. but it is difficult to find a good plan now. 14. c3 dxc3 15. bxc3 Qd7 was good for black, as their coordination of pieces is good. 14. f4 b5 15. Bb3 a5 16. c4 dxc3 17. bxc3 Qb6 18. Kh1 a4 is also pleasant for black, as his space advantage grows.

[39 min left] At the beginning of the game Ne4-g5-e6 idea bothered me a lot, and I am sure this threat was visible to Armand. Thus, I almost expected Ng5, even though this is by no means required. Alternatively, 14... Qd7 could have been played. The position is equal. I spent 9 minutes on this move - more then necessary.
